task.summary: HUGE DEBUG IN GROUP COMMUNICATION -Added support for usage of different ports, both ad applicative and middleware level --Made GroupManager be created with Socket instead String (hostname) --Made MessagingMiddleware be created with Socket instead String (hostname) -Divided Main.main into sub-functions for maintainability -Made PrimitiveParser work with ObjectStreams instead of custom interfaces --Deleted NetworkReader.java and NetworkWriter.java --Deleted PrimitiveParserRunnable.writeObjectSafe, readObjectSafe -NodeInfo tracks streams also, not only socket --2 setters for socket, the one with a boolean arg can initialize the streams --Update LeaderGroupManager, OrdinaryGroupManager so to use the correct setters (if the streams has already been created, they shouldn't be created again)
Update VectorClock: renamed, simplified VectorClock.compareTo, added VectorClock.canAccept
Update NodeInfo, NodeInfoTest: smarter OO programming Updated to adapt: - LeaderGroupManager - OrdinaryGroupManager

Update Main, OrdinaryGroupManager: handled protocol exceptions

Delete GroupManagerFactory.java, Update GroupManager: removed unneeded factory
